## Limitations

The report is limited by the availability of up-to-date data and the potential bias in sources that may not fully represent the diversity of perspectives on sexism. Additionally, the complexity of sexism as a social issue means that not all causes and effects can be comprehensively covered in a single report. Further research is needed to explore the intersectionality of sexism with other forms of discrimination, such as racism and classism.